docs.abstract: Critics of President Trump’s drawdown plans said his claim of victory over the Islamic State may have emboldened its fighters and encouraged the suicide bombing that killed 19 people.
docs.snippet: Critics of President Trump’s drawdown plans said his claim of victory over the Islamic State may have emboldened its fighters and encouraged the suicide bombing that killed 19 people.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Four Americans were among 19 people killed in Syria on Wednesday in a suicide bombing that was claimed by the Islamic State, just weeks after President Trump ordered the withdrawal of United States forces and declared that the extremist group had been defeated.

headline.main: ISIS Attack in Syria Kills 4 Americans, Raising New Worries About Troop Withdrawal
headline.print_headline: 4 Americans Die In Syria as ISIS Targets Convoy

docs.abstract: Lawmakers reacted with concern and bewilderment after President Trump again declared that a border security compromise would have to include a wall at the southwestern border.
docs.snippet: Lawmakers reacted with concern and bewilderment after President Trump again declared that a border security compromise would have to include a wall at the southwestern border.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump proclaimed on Thursday that without funding for his wall at the southwestern border, the panel of lawmakers negotiating a broad compromise on border security would be “wasting their time,” issuing what appeared to be an ultimatum even as lawmakers pleaded for a chance to reach a deal that would head off another shutdown.

headline.main: As Trump Demands His Wall, Lawmakers Plead for Space to Negotiate
headline.print_headline: Border Security Talks Have Just Begun, and Already We’re at the Ultimatum Stage

docs.abstract: With 5G networks about to remake the internet, the Trump administration fears decisions made in the next six months on China’s role will resonate for decades.

docs.lead_paragraph: Jeremy Hunt, the British foreign minister, arrived in Washington last week for a whirlwind of meetings facing a critical question: Should Britain risk its relationship with Beijing and agree to the Trump administration’s request to ban Huawei, China’s leading telecommunications producer, from building its next-generation computer and phone networks?

headline.main: In 5G Race With China, U.S. Pushes Allies to Fight Huawei

docs.abstract: Delivering her party’s rebuttal to the State of the Union speech, Ms. Abrams, who nearly became Georgia’s governor, said voter suppression was a threat to democracy.
docs.snippet: Delivering her party’s rebuttal to the State of the Union speech, Ms. Abrams, who nearly became Georgia’s governor, said voter suppression was a threat to democracy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Stacey Abrams, who narrowly lost her race in November to be Georgia’s governor, delivered the Democrats’ official response to President Trump’s State of the Union address on Tuesday night by outlining the party’s vision for lower health care costs and a more inclusive immigration policy, and pressing her case that access to the voting booth should be easier, not harder.

headline.main: Stacey Abrams, in Democrats’ Response, Calls for Ballot Fairness
headline.print_headline: Rejecting ‘Power Grab,’ Abrams Focuses on Voting Rights in Rebuttal

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For public consumption, President Trump planned to use his State of the Union address on Tuesday night to appeal for bipartisan unity. But at a private lunch for television anchors earlier in the day, he offered searing assessments of a host of Democrats.

headline.main: Before Expected Call for Unity, Trump Laced Into Democrats at Lunch for TV Anchors
